Description: Browniecoin is a cryptocurrency and blockchain company that offers open-source peer-to-peer digital coins.
Full Description: All About Brownie Coins Over the last decade, and since its inception in 2011, brownie coins founded by Armen Merikyan, have evolved from the previous novelty Brownie points. Brownie points were an imaginary social currency earned through good deeds done to others. Over the years, a community and cryptocurrency has been established around this idea. Brownie coins were created as a reward system when someone does something deserving a reward. Initially, Brownie points were awarded as novelty points without any monetary value.  Post world war II, brownie stamps were given depending on the purchase of goods. These stamps could later be redeemed for select goods. Brownie stamps or brownie points, were a resemblance of a good deed performed in the society and rewards for purchases made. Brownie points have since carried on to represent a remittance system with a monetary value attached to each coin earned. Brownie coins have established themselves as part of the cryptocurrency and blockchain narrative that forms a significant part of today’s economy. Brownie coins are an opensource digital currency. Instead of awarding someone brownie points with no value, brownie coins now offer a monetary value.  About Armen Merikyan Armen Merikyan grew up in Los Angeles California, a software designer and a crypto currency early adopter. He is the founder of Brownie Coins which is a digital currency platform. He commenced his venture while working in one of the three biggest entertainment studios in LA, such as Walt Disney, Warner Brothers etc... His passion regarding attempting to actualize bitcoin reproduction was complex as he had no insight of the technical world of crypto currency and blockchain technology. He worked in Silicon Valley where he approached numerous individuals to create a model for a given timetable, price and a full operational help group around the product. He secured funding from his parents, family and friends. This seed money assisted him with creating brownie coins as fully developed digital currency.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US

Description: Born for e-commerce. We provide order fulfillment, distribution, warehousing, packaging, and kitting/assembly services.
Full Description: A DIFFERENT FULFILLMENT EXPERIENCE Having grown and worked with countless e-commerce-focused companies, we saw a need for a different fulfillment experience. Warehousing and logistics shouldn’t be a commodity, but a service that can surprise & delight customers. With the rise of e-commerce over the past few years, many cracks were exposed in how traditional 3PLs were managing and fulfilling orders. Like Grandpa trying to use tik-tok to stay current, these industry titans were unable to keep pace with the growing demands of businesses shifting their focus to online marketplaces. As a result, many of these companies were hindered in their ability to scale. After doing a deep dive into what today’s online businesses were faced with, our team went to work on building a different fulfillment experience – One that would put an emphasis on surprising and delighting the brands we serve. Pitted Logistics was born out of love and a lot of listening. Pitted Logistics is committed to serving our clients to the highest level of service possible. We are technology-driven, service-oriented, people-focused, and stay on the bleeding edge of industry trends. Unlike traditional 3PLs, we are actively engaged in all aspects of the e-commerce world through our sister companies and proprietary technology, Pitted Labs, Pitted Ventures, and Atlas. This enables us to be a complete partner to your success beyond just fulfillment.

Industries: Assisted Living, Computer Vision, Elder Care
Description: Heron Point Tech build tech-based amenities to enhance the assisted living experience
Full Description: Between 2015 and 2030, the number of people in the world aged 60 years or over is expected to grow by 56%, from just over 900 million to nearly 1.5 billion. This trend in turn leads to an increase in the number of people requiring long-term skilled care (LTSC), which includes home care, hospices, nursing homes, and assisted living centers. One of the most common issues in LTSC settings is falls. One in every 3 people older than 65 years is estimated to fall 1 or more times each year. Fall death rates among adults age 65 and older increased more than 30% from 2007 to 2016. Every 19 minutes, an older adult dies from a fall. Falls in older adults are not only risky, but also costly. In 2019, falls of US residents aged 65 or older led to $51B in medical costs, with $39B paid for by Medicare/Medicaid and $12B paid by private entities. Falls are also the 2nd largest reason for lawsuits against LTSCs. Heron Point Tech’s Fall Prevention System allows assisted living facilities to preemptively and continuously detect residents who are likely to fall. As opposed to most fall-related systems, our system doesn’t detect falls - it stops them from happening in the first place. By using our camera-based system to track resident walking patterns/gaits, residents are assigned weekly fall risk scores. No wearable devices required.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
